Filter latent dimensions

Source: R/output_utils.R
dot-filter_output_dimensions.Rd

Filters latent dimensions by name in the output of an integration method.

Usage

.filter_output_dimensions(
  method_output,
  latent_dimensions,
  fixed_length = NULL,
  method_name = attr(method_output, "method")
)

Arguments

method_output

Integration method output generated via the get_output() function.

latent_dimensions

Character vector giving the latent dimensions to retain in the method's output.

fixed_length

Integer, expected length of latent_dimensions. If NULL (default value), the length of latent_dimensions will not be checked.

method_name

Character, name of the method to use in the error message.

Value

Similar to method_output, but the samples score table or features weight table have been filtered.
